aragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As an example, now less than a tenth of the files rebuilt after a module changes resulting in a one-third speedup.  Incremental builds."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The first part of the compiler (the driver) is now written in Swift.  It is now the default."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Memory-Management","text":"Memory Management"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Class instances use ARC (automatic reference counting)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The compiler now uses a smarter way to track references and can eliminate retain release traffic."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Improves runtime and code size but is an compiler option ‚ÄúOptimize Object Lifetimes‚Äù","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There is a session about this.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Ergonomic-improvements","text":"Ergonomic improvements"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-evolution\/blob\/be686706919cab796b47b8c528a1fa52028a8335\/proposals\/0284-multiple-variadic-parameters.md","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":": Multiple variadic parameters"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-evolution\/blob\/be686706919cab796b47b8c528a1fa52028a8335\/proposals\/0287-implicit-member-chains.md","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":": Implicit member chains"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-evolution\/blob\/be686706919cab796b47b8c528a1fa52028a8335\/proposals\/0289-result-builders.md","type":"reference"},{"text":": Result builders","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-evolution\/blob\/be686706919cab796b47b8c528a1fa52028a8335\/proposals\/0293-extend-property-wrappers-to-function-and-closure-parameters.md","type":"reference"},{"text":": Property wrappers on parameters","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-evolution\/blob\/be686706919cab796b47b8c528a1fa52028a8335\/proposals\/0295-codable-synthesis-for-enums-with-associated-values.md","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":": Codable synthesis for associated value enums","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-evolution\/blob\/be686706919cab796b47b8c528a1fa52028a8335\/proposals\/0299-extend-generic-static-member-lookup.md","type":"reference"},{"text":": Static member lookup in generic contexts","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-evolution\/blob\/be686706919cab796b47b8c528a1fa52028a8335\/proposals\/0307-allow-interchangeable-use-of-double-cgfloat-types.md","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":": Interchangeable use of CGFloat and Double"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-evolution\/blob\/be686706919cab796b47b8c528a1fa52028a8335\/proposals\/0309-unlock-existential-types-for-all-protocols.md","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":": #if for postfix member expressions","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The SE standards for Swift Evolution."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"What follows is a series of examples of how these features can simplify your code."}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Result builders was refined over the year and now has a whole session devoted to it.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Making enums with associated values "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Codable"},{"type":"text","text":", instead of being pages of boilerplate is now just adding "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Codable"},{"type":"text","text":" and letting the compiler do the work."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Flexible-static-member-lookup","text":"Flexible static member lookup"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["protocol Coffee { ... }","struct RegularCoffee: Coffee {}","struct Cappuccino: Coffee {}","","extension Coffee where Self == Cappucino {","  static var cappucino: Cappucino = { Cappucino() }","}","","func brew<CoffeeType: Coffee>(_: CoffeeType) { ... }","","brew(.cappucino.large)   \/\/ Beautify enum-like syntax!"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Improved-property-wrappers","text":"Improved property wrappers"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can use property wrappers can now be used on function (and closures) parameters.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"SwiftUI-example","text":"SwiftUI example"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The before and after is pretty remarkable!","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In Swift you can pass a binding to SwiftUI ","type":"text"},{"code":"List","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to get access to the projection and wrapped value.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There is a session about this.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It makes your code simpler!"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Asynchronous-and-Concurrent-Programming","text":"Asynchronous and Concurrent Programming"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Synchronous: code statements execute one-by-one and in-order","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Asynchronous: code suspends execution waiting for op to finish, then continues","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Concurrent: multiple code statements executing at once","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Without Swift‚Äôs new features you often write async code using completion handlers (closure)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Later, after the network request finishes, the callback happens.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Only then can you deal with errors, which can be awkward.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"URLSession"},{"text":"‚Äôs ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dataTask"},{"text":" is changed to this:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let (data, response) = try await URLSession.shared.data(for: request)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The await will suspend the operation but ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"not"}]},{"text":" block the thread so other","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"work can continue on that thread.  This allows a small number of threads","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to be shared among several asynchronous processes.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The code can then continue inline making it easy to follow."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are other sessions about this."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Concurrency","text":"Concurrency"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Concurrency builds on the async\/await idea.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["func titleImage() async throws -> Image {","  async let background = renderBackground()","  async let foreground = renderForeground()","  let title = try renderTitle()","  return try await merge(background, foreground, title)","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"async let"},{"type":"text","text":" spawns off another concurrent operation."},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"merge"},{"type":"text","text":" operation has to be marked with an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"await"},{"type":"text","text":" to signal that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this thread may suspend.  This function "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"will not return","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" until the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"background tasks complete.  Even if an error is thrown, Swift"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will ensure everything completes before returning."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift will signal unfinished tasks that an error was thrown as an optimization."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The Structured concurrency in Swift session describes this in greater detail."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Actors","text":"Actors"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is another concurrency construct that helps you manage shared mutable data.  Here is an example"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that will corrupt if accessed from multiple threads:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["class Statistics {","  private var counter: Int = 0","  func increment() {","    counter += 1","  }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The fix is simple.  Change ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["actor Statistics {","  private var counter: Int = 0","  func increment() {","    counter += 1","  }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Swift compiler prevents corruption by suspending operations"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"until it is safe to make the change.  That is why you typically"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"need to call them with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"await"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"They also work with async\/await."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Actors are like classes (reference types) but allow the Swift compiler","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and runtime to protect against data races.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is a full session about this."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Future-of-Swift-6","text":"Future of Swift 6"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"async\/await\/actors is a basis"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift 6 will have additional capability enable ‚ÄúSafe concurrency‚Äù","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Make concurrent programming just as hard as normal programming","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"More efficiency","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Make Swift 6 better by telling swift.org about your experiences!","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can try a new compiler toolchain!","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Participate in the forums"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Participate in the mentorship program.","type":"text"},{"tex